    "summary": "Assistant professor / lecturer in comparative arts & media studies, programme director MA Comparative Arts & Media Studies (http://masters.vu.nl/en/programmes/arts-culture-comparative-arts-media-studies/index.aspx). Former editor Tijdschrift voor Mediageschiedenis (TMG). Formerly art history student (Utrecht/Leiden), film archivist (Filmmuseum), PhD (UvA Amsterdam), guest lecturer (University of Siena, Italy), guest researcher (Royal Dutch Institute, Rome), and guest curator (Fries Museum, Leeuwarden). For specialties and interests see below.\n\nBetween September 2020 and January 2021 I will be a Research Fellow at the NIAS (Netherlands Institute for Advances Study in the Humanities and Social Sciences).\n\nSpecialties: Visual culture, intermediality, film history, film & art, film & graphic design, film & architecture, Italian cinema, Luchino Visconti, Antiquity & film, silent cinema, Dutch cinema, cinema exhibition & distribution, cross-medial exhibitions, museum studies\n\nHomepage & blog: www.ivoblom.nl.\nHomepage university: https://research.vu.nl/en/persons/ivo-blom.\nPublications: www.ivoblom.nl, www.academia.edu.\nMA Comparative Arts and Media Studies: vu/comparativearts.",
